<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Immigration Act of 1924's quota system was designed to:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Promote diversity</option>
            <option letter="b">Favor Northern European immigration</option>
            <option letter="c">Increase Asian immigration</option>
            <option letter="d">Welcome Southern Europeans</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Immigration Act of 1924's quota system was specifically designed to favor immigrants from Northern and Western Europe while severely restricting immigration from Southern and Eastern Europe. Based on 2% of each nationality's population in the 1890 census, the system deliberately chose a year before large-scale immigration from Southern and Eastern Europe began, while completely excluding Asian immigration.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
